We are a micro loans organization created by producers and indigenous Tseltal producers. We are located in the northern jungle of Chiapas and we are part of the Yomol A'tel group.
In this social enterprise we seek to build an alternative sensible to the needs of credit access that are required in our region.
We are trying to challenging the ways of thinking of credit and microfinances
We seek to generate new financial capacities, always taking into account the conditions of the territory and its context.
Comon Sit Ca'teltic is an economic engine which distributes the resources generated to where they are needed.
We seek to generate new financial capacities, always taking into account the conditions of the territory and its context.
A commitment to a social and solidarity economy.

We live in Mexico, in the north of the state of Chiapas, among the mountains covering the municipalities of Chilón, Sitalá, Yajalón, Pantelho and Ocosingo. The tropical climate makes the area suitable for the cultivation of coffee under shade (main source of income for our families). However our main sustenance is the cultivation of plots: corn, bean and a variety of fruits are the basis of our food and our families economy.

Throughout this area, Maya Tseltal culture prevails, which retains great cultural richness through our language, our traditions and our system of civil and religious cargos. All this, along with the care of Mother Earth, allows us to maintain what we call
(Good life and harmony) with our community, with the environment and with our spirituality.
This region is one of the most impoverished in Mexico. Despite being an area with great natural riches, it is other people who benefit from it the most.
That is why we decided to organize, and escape from the depence of harmful economic processes and started building our own.
Yomol A'tel means in the Tseltal language
Together we work, we walk, we dream
. He is an imaging group by social and cooperative companies, as well as the producing families of the North Selva region of Chiapas and collaborators at various parts of the Mexican Republic.

We focus on generating answers from the social base to build alternatives of value aggregation in the resources that we currently have in our territory, always taking care of our relationship with Mother Earth and accompanied by various social actors that coincide with our vocation (universities, foundations , investors, consumers and other social experiences, among others).
Agroecological production, transformation, export of finished product and sale in cup.
Handmade soaps, shampoo, creams and crafts.
Microcredits for consumption and production for families that are part of Yomol A'Tel.
Agroecological production and national sale, early stage of transformation of the finished product.

Comon Sit Ca'tetic started with reinvesting part of the benefit that brought the built price of coffee. From there we seek to use those resources to start new activities that in turn generate gains that are reinvested again to finance other productive activities.
The process has been attentive to the economic-productive dynamics that can be encouraged in a family, in a community or region.
As the project was growing in size and complexity, and remote data access was increasingly important, we started the development of this site.
comonsitcateltic.com is a multi-language platform that has opened us new possibilities, allowing us to better explore our data and work forms in a process that we continue to explore and improve.
We consider it important to share our experience, so for those interested in seeing, copying, downloading or improving our code, they can do it freely
The code of this platform has been developed in a process together with our collaborator and friends
Map and data of the region
In the process of building this platform we found a lot of data from the region that we consider will be of public interest.
During the next few months, in support with volunteers and enthusiasts we will be building a free access map with information from the region.
